President Donald J. Trump has announced the creation of a bipartisan Presidential Commission on Election Integrity through an executive order. Vice President Mike Pence will serve as Chairman and Kansas Secretary of State Kris Kobach will be the Vice-Chair of the Commission. The Commission will focus on studying vulnerabilities in voting systems used for federal elections that could lead to improper voter registrations, improper voting, fraudulent voter registrations, and fraudulent voting. It will also address concerns about voter suppression and other voting irregularities. The Commission will utilize state and federal databases to gather necessary data. The work of the Commission is expected to take a year, with a report to be issued in 2018.